The paper presents a deep learning model for anomaly detection in beehives using sensor data. This involves analyzing behavioral patterns and detecting unusual events, which are typical tasks in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of sensors and data analysis also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and internet of things (cs.IOT). Finally, the paper discusses the potential economic impact of detecting anomalies, which relates to systems and control (cs.SY).
